This paper is about building dialog agents that can converse naturally with humans, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and artificial intelligence (AI). The paper specifically focuses on integrating commonsense knowledge into end-to-end conversational models, which involves machine learning and deep learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
